@node GUI "Describing the graphic user interface"

Much work has been done to make the graphic user interface intuitive and easy to use.  Here are some of its features:

@{fg shine}o@{fg text} Multi-window environment.  The windows work independently of each other and are 'multitasking'.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} All windows are font-adaptable and sizeable.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} The program can either display its windows on the Workbench, on the default public screen or open an own screen of any resolution, size and depth.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} Most gadgets have keyboard equivalents for easy execution.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} The windows will remember it's attributes when closed and reopened.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} All environment attributes may be saved to disk.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} On-line help for all windows, gadgets and menu-items.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} Image buttons where appropriate.
@{fg shine}o@{fg text} EasyRexx comes with several nice fonts which look good on both non-interlaced and interlaced screens.

@{fg shine}Listview control@{fg text}
Listviews may be controlled using the arrow-keys
Cursor up/down - previous/next item
Shift Cursor up/down - previous/next page
Control Cursor up/down - top/bottom item
Alt Cursor up/down - top/bottom item
or pressing the vanilla key that is underlined in the border group title.  Pressing the vanilla key will jump to the next item.  The previous item may be selected by holding down any shift button and then press the vanilla key.

@{fg shine}NOTE@{fg text}
A gadget-shortcut may be cancelled by pressing another key or the alt-qualifier while holding the shortcut-key down.

@{fg shine}Screen notification support@{fg text}
Whenever screennotify.library is available in libs the ARexx Interface Designer will make use of this library.  This means that the Designer will automatically close and reopen its windows whenever the visiting screen is closed or its pubscreen attributes changes.


See also @{" Settings menu " link Menu_3}
@endnode

