@node codewindow "Code settings"

This window contain switches and data that affects how the generated  source will act.

@{fg shine}Main code@{fg text}
When checked, source for main code will be generated, making the source directly compilable.

@{fg shine}AREXX handler @{fg text}
When checked, an ARexx handler function will be generated.  The handler will handle all incoming ARexx commands.  The handler may be of different types depending on the handler type selected (see Handle).

@{fg shine}Templates @{fg text}
When checked, templates for all ARexx functions will be created.  This checkbox is only available when the Handle is set to 'Call functions'.

@{fg shine}By IDs@{fg text}
When selected, the ARexx handler will handle ARexx commands by their ID.

@{fg shine}Call functions @{fg text}
When selected, the ARexx handler will handle ARexx commands by calling the ARexx function defined in the context->userdata field.

@{fg shine}Author @{fg text}
Name of author.  This string may be retrieved from the ARexx script using GET AUTHOR.

@{fg shine}Copyright @{fg text}
Copyright string.  This string may be retrieved from the ARexx script using GET COPYRIGHT.

@{fg shine}Version @{fg text}
Version string.  This string may be retrieved from the ARexx script using GET VERSION.

@{fg shine}Portname @{fg text}
Name of ARexx port which your application will receive ARexx commands through.
@endnode

************************************************************************
@node macrowindow "Macro settings"

Beginning with V3.0, EasyRexx features a set of functions to create, record, run, read and write ARexx macros.  ARexx Interface Designer takes full advantage of these new functions and offers advanced macro control of the designer utility.

The macro window and menu allow the user to set up a default of 10 ARexx macros.  The macros themselves may be entered directly into the macrostring or selected from a file requester.  When entered, the macro name will be displayed in the ARexx menu.

An ARexx macro can be run by selecting the macro name in the ARexx menu or by selecting one of the numbered gadgets in the macro window.


See also @{" ARexx commands " link arexx}
@endnode

