@node Menu_3 "Settings menu"

@{fg shine}Acknowledge@{fg text}
If checked, the ARexx Interface Designer will inform you when the last changes done to the project have not been saved.  You will be given the peritonitic to save before proceeding.

@{fg shine}Save when exit?@{fg text}
If checked, the current GUI settings will be saved to ENVARC: when you quit.  The current settings is always saved to ENV:, but this will be lost when rebooting the machine.

@{fg shine}Simple refresh@{fg text}
If checked, all windows will be opened in simple refresh mode.  Simple refresh mode use less memory than smart refresh, but the window update is slower.

@{fg shine}Close Workbench@{fg text}
If checked, the ARexx Interface Designer will try to close the Workbench screen to save memory.  The Workbench screen cannot be closed if there other applications are blocking the Workbench screen.

@{fg shine}Own screen@{fg text}
If checked, ARexx Interface Designer will open an own public screen on which it's windows will be opened.  This item is included to prevent a messy Workbench screen.  Other applications may open a window on this screen using (in most cases) the tooltype 'Pubscreen='.

@{fg shine}Backdrop@{fg text}
If this item is checked, the main window will be opened as a backdrop window and appear behind all other ARexx Interface Designer windows.

@{fg shine}Shanghai@{fg text}
If this item and the 'Own screen' item are checked, the Designer will install itself as the system's default public screen.  Other applications that support public screens will now be opened on this screen.

@{fg shine}Use screen's font@{fg text}
If checked, the ARexx Interface Designer will use the screen font of the current public screen.

@{fg shine}Select font...@{fg text}
Default font for the ARexx Interface Designer.  Will become available when 'Use screen's font' is not checked.

@{fg shine}Select screenmode...@{fg text}
Default screenmode for the ARexx Interface Designer.  Will become available when 'Own screen' is checked.

@{fg shine}Adjust palette...@{fg text}
Default palette for the ARexx Interface Designer.  Will become available when 'Own screen' is checked.

@{fg shine}Open...@{fg text}
Opens a environment settings file.

@{fg shine}Save@{fg text}
Saves the current settings as default.

@{fg shine}Save as...@{fg text}
Lets you save the environment settings under another name.
