@node arexx_format "Format used"
All ARexx commands are described using the format shown below:

@{fg shine}@{fg shine}Synopsis@{fg text}@{fg text}
Name of command and arguments.  ARexx command names and switches are given in upper case while values are given in lower case and also underlined.    Values are meant to be replaced by a number or a string depending on the ARexx command in question.  Arguments that are not absolutely necessary are placed have brackets '[ ]' around them.

@{fg shine}Alias@{fg text}
Gives alias for the command.  This alias can be used instead of the real command name.  This description is omitted if there are no aliases for the command.

@{fg shine}Arguments@{fg text}
Describes each argument known to the command.

@{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
Describes what is the purpose of the command.

@{fg shine}Returns@{fg text}
Describes what the command returns.  This description is omitted if the command doesn't return something.

@{fg shine}Examples@{fg text}
Gives examples on the usage of the command and its parameters.

@endnode

