@node arexx_getattr "GETATTR"

@{fg shine}Synopsis@{fg text}
GETATTR @{u}variable@{uu}

@{fg shine}Arguments@{fg text}
@{u}variable@{uu} must be one of the following: ALWAYS, KEYWORD, MULTIPLE, NUMBER, SWITCH, TOGGLE, FINAL, ARGUMENT, COMMAND, AUTHOR, COPYRIGHT, VERSION, PORTNAME, MAIN, AREXXHANDLER, TEMPLATES, HANDLERTYPE.

@{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
Gets the value of a variable from the AREXX Interface Designer.  The value or string will be accessible through the reserved RESULT variable, provided that your AREXX script has 'OPTIONS RESULTS' at the beginning of the script.

@{fg shine}Returns@{fg text}
ALWAYS
returns 1 if the Always checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

KEYWORD
returns 1 if the Keyword checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

MULTIPLE
returns 1 if the Multiple checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

NUMBER
returns 1 if the Number checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

SWITCH
returns 1 if the Switch checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

TOGGLE
returns 1 if the Toggle checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

FINAL
returns 1 if the Final checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

ARGUMENT
returns the name of the currently selected argument.

COMMAND
returns the name of the currently selected command.

AUTHOR
returns the author string.

COPYRIGHT
returns the copyright string.

VERSION
returns the version string.

PORTNAME
returns the portname string.

MAIN
returns 1 if the Generate source: Main checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

AREXXHANDLER
returns 1 if the Generate source: AREXX Handler checkgadget is checked, 0 if not.

TEMPLATES
returns 1 if the Templates checkbutton is checked, 0 if not.

HANDLER
returns the type of handler selected.

@{fg shine}Examples@{fg text}
GETATTR VERSION
GETATTR ARGUMENT
GETATTR ALWAYS
@endnode


