@node arexx_request "REQUEST"

@{fg shine}Synopsis@{fg text}
REQUEST @{u}title@{uu} @{u}text@{uu} @{u}buttons@{uu}

@{fg shine}Arguments@{fg text}
@{u}title@{uu}
Requester title

@{u}text@{uu}
Text that will be displayed in the requester.  Lines is seperated by a '\n' character.

@{u}buttons@{uu}
Text or requester buttons.  If you want the requester to contain more than one button you can seperate them with a '|' character.

@{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
Displays a query requester which the user must satisfy before the next macro command can be executed.

@{fg shine}Returns@{fg text}
0 if the user selected the rightmost button.  Any other number indicates the button number from the left, for example will the button string "OK|Button1|Button2|Cancel" return 0 if 'Cancel' was selected, 1 if 'OK' was selected, 2 if 'Button1' was selected and so on...

@{fg shine}Examples@{fg text}
REQUEST '"Title" "This is a test" "OK"'
REQUEST '"Title" "Press a button" "OK|Cancel"'
@endnode

