@node tooltypes "Tooltypes"

The ARexx Interface Designer will understand the tooltypes listed below.  They may be entered in the ARexx Interface Designer's icon by selecting the Information item in the Workbench's Icon menu or by typing them in at the prompt in a Shell window.

@{fg shine}AUTHOR=<name>@{fg text}
Name of author that will appear in the Author string gadget in the Code window.

@{fg shine}COPYRIGHT=<copyright>@{fg text}
Copyright string that will appear in the Code window.

@{fg shine}FROM=<project>@{fg text}
Project to open at startup.

@{fg shine}LANGUAGE=<language>@{fg text}
Name of language that the ARexx Interface Designer will use.

@{fg shine}MACROS=<macrofile>@{fg text}
ARexx macro file that will be opened at startup.

@{fg shine}PORTNAME=<name>@{fg text}
Name of port that will appear in the Code window.

@{fg shine}PUBSCREEN=<name>@{fg text}
Name of public screen that the ARexx Interface Designer will open its window on.

@{fg shine}VERSION=<version>@{fg text}
Version string that will appear in the Code window.	
@endnode

